text: Emily Thouy is a French karateka. In 2016, she became world champion in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2016 World Karate Championships held in Linz, Austria. In 2015, she won the gold medal in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2015 European Games held in Baku, Azerbaijan. In the final, she defeated Jelena Kovačević of Croatia. In 2017, she competed in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2017 World Games held in Wrocław, Poland.
